rComments: Dr Roncadin was a great professor who was always enthusiastic, knowledgable and made our classes super interesting.  I would highly recommend taking her classes!

She presents interesting lectures however she does not know how to evaluate students. Her tests m/c are based on memorizing a 500 page book in detail. For the test S/A there were many possible correct answers but only the ones that were on strict rubric were right. The paper had vague guidelines. So interesting class but more work than its worth

She is a great lecturer, but going to the lectures isn't needed(but you will likely want to go). Her multiple choice are incredibly specific and difficult (needing to know certain percentages). She is a great professor, kind, and approachable. Just difficult to gage important information and such.

She is the best professor or teacher I have ever had. She's super kind, intelligent and always ready to help. Explains everything perfectly and I would take every single one of her classes. PSY341 was great and her seminar course is amazing as well (PSY440). I'm really glad I met her. By far best person I've met in university, she's perfect!

She's such a great prof.Makes lectures super interesting by adding videos, talking about her own clinical experiences, and asking students about their opinions on a certain topic. Very approachable. Her MC is a bit on the hard side, but tests are fair overall. I strongly recommend her class.
